getting regular hot tub time to continue these tests and see, so far no yellowing or permanent cloudiness. We believe this could change after years of use, or with higher/longer durations of heat. So far we see no color change with short spurts of boiling, as is normal 6/7

What does this mean for Near Clear? Short periods of increased heat may cause cloudiness, but toys should revert back to their former clarity after a few hours or a day has passed. We don't know if this effect will differ after repeated exposure. The test frogs are now 5/7
